The distribution of S. populnea lapponica ssp. n. is within the distribution of Salix lapponum in Fennoscandia (
Hulten 1971
). The most southern populations of S. populnea lapponica ssp. n. occur near Trysil, Norway, while the most northern populations occur north of the Arctic Circle (Fig. 13). Since Salix lapponum is distributed eastwards in Siberia approximately to the Jenisej Valley (
Hulten and Fries 1986
), it is possible that S. populnea lapponica ssp. n. has a much wider distribution in Russia than we are able to show in the present paper.
